A vintage-style illustration of a well-worn leather travel suitcase covered in colorful destination stickers from Munich, Hamburg, and Düsseldorf, sitting on a cobblestone street with the blurred silhouette of traditional German architecture in the background. The scene is bathed in warm, nostalgic sepia tones with hints of amber and deep brown. Steam rises from a nearby coffee cup resting on the cobblestones, suggesting a pause between journeys. The composition evokes the romance of European business travel and professional gatherings, with subtle details like a folded conference program peeking out of the suitcase pocket and train tickets scattered nearby. The lighting mimics aged photograph paper with soft vignetting around the edges.
